1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,851
Four, practice speaking up.

2
00:00:03,120 --> 00:00:15,091
In working with many kinds of groups of all sizes, I've watched many persons with keen perception and much native ability freeze and fail to participate in discussions.

3
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:19,411
It isn't that these folks don't want to get in and wade with the rest.

4
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:22,371
Rather, it's a simple lack of confidence.

5
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:28,051
The conference clam thinks to himself, my opinion is probably worthless.

6
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:31,331
If I say something, I'll probably look foolish.

7
00:00:31,520 --> 00:00:33,170
I'll just say nothing.

8
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:40,130
Besides, the others in the group probably know more than I. I don't want the others to know how ignorant I am.

9
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:47,170
Each time the conference clam fails to speak, he feels even more inadequate, more inferior.

10
00:00:47,440 --> 00:00:52,690
Often he makes a faint promise to himself, that deep down he knows he won't keep,

11
00:00:52,880 --> 00:00:54,610
to speak next time.

12
00:00:55,120 --> 00:00:56,770
This is very important.

13
00:00:56,960 --> 00:01:03,170
Each time our clam fails to speak, he takes one more dose of confidence poison.

14
00:01:03,281 --> 00:01:06,451
He becomes less and less confident of himself.

15
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:12,531
But on the positive side, the more you speak up, the more you add to your confidence,

16
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:15,491
and the easier it is to speak up the next time.

17
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:16,931
Speak up.

18
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:19,571
It's a confidence-building vitamin.

19
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:22,451
Put this confidence builder to use.

20
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:26,690
Make it a rule to speak up at every open meeting you attend.

21
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:28,051
Speak up.

22
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:34,851
Say something voluntarily at every business conference, committee meeting, community forum you attend.

23
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:36,371
Make no exception.

24
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:42,291
Comment, make a suggestion, ask a question, and don't be the last to speak.

25
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:46,371
Try to be the icebreaker, the first one in with a comment.

26
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:49,250
And never worry about looking foolish.

27
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:50,210
You won't.

28
00:01:50,321 --> 00:01:55,250
For each person who doesn't agree with you, odds are another person will.

29
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:59,411
Quit asking yourself, I wonder if I dare speak.

30
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:05,650
Instead, concentrate on getting the discussion leader's attention so you can speak.

31
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:12,531
For special training and experience in speaking, consider joining your local Toastmasters club.

32
00:02:12,801 --> 00:02:21,730
Thousands of conscientious people have developed confidence through a planned program to feel at ease talking with people and to people.

